<p>This question is different than the suggested duplicate because I am both checking for errors and not getting any return value.</p>  <p>I'm testing a simple web app locally with apache and mysql. When I try to execute any SQL command with PDO, it fails silently. I've turned on exceptions and wrapped it in a try/catch, but still I get no error messages of any kind, the page with this script is simply blank and nothing happens in my database.</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?php     try{         $dbhost = "localhost";         $dbuser = "root";         $dbpassword = "****";         $dbname = "****";          $db = new PDO("mysql:host=$dbhost;dbname=$dbname", $dbuser, $dbpassword);         $db-&gt;setAttribute(PDO::ATTR_ERRMODE, PDO::ERRMODE_EXCEPTION);          $query = "INSERT INTO USERS (Name) VALUES ('Bob')";         $db-&gt;prepare($query);         $db-&gt;execute();     }     catch (Exception $e){         die($e);     } ?&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The USERS table:</p>  <pre><code>CREATE TABLE USERS(     UID INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,     Name varchar(100) NOT NULL, INDEX(Name), UNIQUE(Name),     Email varchar(100) NOT NULL, INDEX(Email), UNIQUE(Email),     Hash varchar(100) NOT NULL,     Salt varchar(100) NOT NULL ); </code></pre>